Hancock accuses those still socialising in UK of being 'very selfish' Read moreIn the UK we have had nine weeks to listen, learn and prepare.
The UK’s head start in managing the outbreak continued as our confirmed case count remained lower than our neighbours’.
So, at the end of week, the UK government did a 180-degree turn, reversing what it had said only days previously.
We also need to backtrack and start doing the mass testing, tracing and isolating that are integral to breaking chains of transmission.
• Prof Devi Sridhar is chair of global public health at the University of Edinburgh